Executive Profile
Norman H. Wesley  Chairman of Fortune Brands Inc, CEO of Fortune Brands Inc and Director of Fortune Brands Inc, Therma-Tru Corp.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships67--
Background

		Mr. Norman H. Wesley, also known as Norm, served as the Chief Executive Officer at Beam Suntory Inc. (formerly Beam Inc.) from December 1999 to January 2008 and served as its President and Chief Operating Officer since 1999. Mr. Wesley served as the Chief Executive Officer of Fortune Brands Home & Office, Inc. from 1997 to 1999. He joined Fortune Brands in 1984. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer at Fortune Brands since January 1999 and served as its ... Vice President of Corporate Development since 1987. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Fortune Brands, Inc. since December 1999 until December 2007 and served as its Chairman since December 1999 until September 2008. Mr. Wesley began his career at Crown Zellerbach Corporation, where over a ten-year period he held various management positions, including Vice President and General Manager of the Office Products Group. From 1997 to December 31, 1998, he served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of MasterBrands Industries Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of ACCO World Corporation from 1990 to 1997. He led Beam Inc. office products unit for 10 years. He has been the Chairman at Green Mountain Coffee Roasters Inc. since December 12, 2012. He serves as the Chairman of Junior Achievement of Chicago. He served as the Chairman of Beam Suntory Inc. from December 1999 to September 2008. He served as Chairman of the Board at Keurig Green Mountain, Inc. since December 2012. He has been a Director at Acushnet Holdings Corp. since 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Acuity Brands, Inc. since January 7, 2011, Fortune Brands Home & Security, Inc. since September 15, 2011 and Green Mountain Coffee Roasters since July 31, 2012. He served as a Director at Keurig Green Mountain, Inc. since August 2012. He served as Director of Beam Suntory Inc. since 1999. He served as Presiding Independent Director at ACCO Brands Corporation since May 7, 2013 until May 13, 2014 and served as its Director since August 2005 until May 13, 2014. Mr. Wesley served as an Independent Director of R.R. Donnelley & Sons Company from 2001 to May 2008. He served as a Director of Enable Holdings, Inc. since November 1998 and Pactiv LLC (formerly Pactiv Corp.) from December 2001 to November 16, 2010. He serves as a Trustee at the Glenwood School and the Lake Forest Academy. He serves on the Board of the Executives' Club of Chicago. He serves on the Civic Committee of the Commercial Club of Chicago. He is a recipient of the ADL's Torch of Liberty Award and the City of Hope's Spirit of Life Award. Mr. Wesley has a BS in Finance and an MBA from the University of Utah.Read Full Background




